  "texts": [
    "Lin's enhancement suggests that the similarity between two concepts is determined by the extent to which they share information.",
    "In this approach, Lin incorporated not only the IC of the Least Common Ancestor of the compared concepts but also included the IC values of the concepts themselves in the measurement.",
    "Conventional IC methods combine hierarchical structure and usage statistics to compute IC values, which can be computationally expensive.",
    "Seco et al. [41] proposed an intrinsic measure that relies solely on the hierarchical structure (taxonomy) without involving statistics.",
    "This approach experimentally outperforms traditional IC similarity methods.In feature-based approaches, the representation of concepts to be compared is done through a set of features."
  ],
